What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 113937 loan case in the dataset with about 80 features . Most variables are numeric in nature, but the variables CreditGrade, LoanStatus, ProsperRating (Alpha), and EmploymentStatus are ordered factor variables with the following levels.

The system of loan assesment is divided into two parts:¶

  • Before 2009
  • After 2009

From lowest to highest (oldest to newest):

  • Credit Grade: 'NC', 'HR', 'E', 'D', 'C', 'B', 'A', 'AA'

  • Loan Status: Current, successfull, risky (anything that is Chargedoff, defaulted, past due, or cancelled)

  • Prosper Rating (Alpha): 'HR', 'E', 'D', 'C', 'B', 'A', 'AA'

  • Employment Status: 'Not available', 'Other', 'Not employed','Retired', 'Part-time', 'Employed', 'Full-time'

  • Income Range: '0','Not employed', '1-24,999','25,000-49,999', '50,000-74,999', '75,000-99,999', '100,000+'

  • ProsperRating (Alpha) : 'HR', 'E', 'D', 'C', 'B', 'A', 'AA'

  • Loan Origination Quarter: 'Q4 2005', 'Q3 2006', 'Q4 2006', 'Q2 2006', 'Q1 2006', 'Q3 2007', 'Q1 2007', 'Q4 2007', 'Q2 2007', 'Q3 2008', 'Q1 2008', 'Q2 2008', 'Q4 2008', 'Q3 2009', 'Q4 2009', 'Q2 2009', 'Q2 2010', 'Q4 2010', 'Q1 2010', 'Q3 2010', 'Q4 2011', 'Q2 2011', 'Q1 2011', 'Q3 2011', 'Q4 2012', 'Q2 2012', 'Q1 2012', 'Q3 2012', 'Q3 2013', 'Q4 2013', 'Q2 2013', 'Q1 2013', 'Q1 2014'

# This function should remove highly correlated descriptors(columns) from any dataset with specified correlation threshold
def correlation(dataset, threshold):
    """ Removes all columns with internal correlation with each other if they are than the specified 'threshold' """
    col_corr = set() # Set of all the names of deleted columns
    corr_matrix = dataset.corr()
    for i in range(len(corr_matrix.columns)):
        for j in range(i):
            if (corr_matrix.iloc[i, j] >= threshold or corr_matrix.iloc[i, j] <= -threshold) and (corr_matrix.columns[j] not in col_corr):
                colname = corr_matrix.columns[i] # getting the name of column
                col_corr.add(colname)
                if colname in dataset.columns:
                    del dataset[colname] # deleting the column from the dataset

    print(dataset.columns)

def boxgrid(x, y, **kwargs):
    """ Quick hack for creating box plots with seaborn's PairGrid. """
    default_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
    sb.boxplot(x=x, y=y, color = default_color)

Not anticipated trends:¶

1 - Credit score for high risk HR clients were higher relatively which indicating that the rating is not very accurate. 2 - Credit score for not employed and retired are higher relatively then working clients but if we look closer we find out that non employed and retired clients request much less loan amounts.`
